@DATABASE "Default"
@Ver$ "FontCode V1.06 (08/12/97)"
@author "Heiko Schröder"
@Index MAIN
@remark requires MultiView

@NODE "Main" "FontCode 1.06 for FinalCopy/Finalwriter"
@TOC "MAIN"

                                @{fg shine}»FontCode 1.06«@{fg text}

            is an ARexx-Script for Finalwriter or FinalCopyII.
              Now you are be able to write exotic ASCII-codes.



                           @{" " link "Install"} Installation

                           @{" " link "Benutz"} Usage

                           @{" " link "Sonst"} Author

                           @{" " link "Hist"} History


 Sorry, for my poor english. If you want, you can translate my german guide
 and send to me. You can find the german guide in the Aminet.

                      biz/swood/fw_font.lha

 Thanks.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"



1. Copy »FontCode.fw« to your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start program »RexxMast«.

3. Start »Finalwriter« or »FinalCopyII«.

4. Open menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - FontCode
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (FontCode.fw)
         * "HotKey" - F10
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutz" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"



            If you need a symbol, load the font, press F10 
            and input the ASCII-Code.

                                    Thats all.
@ENDNODE

